cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for sequence tagging. Specifically, it focuses on low-resource part-of-speech tagging using cross-lingual projection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a novel approach to sequence tagging that involves learning to correct errors from cross-lingual projection, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions using parallel data, which could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
